This paper belongs to the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with analyzing written texts and sentence structures. It also involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in natural language processing. Additionally, the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves analyzing data and comparing different measures. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible category as the paper deals with extracting information from texts. Deep learning (cs.DL) could also be a relevant category as it involves analyzing patterns in data. Finally, cybernetics (cs.CY) could be a possible category as it involves studying systems and feedback mechanisms, which could be relevant to analyzing text structures.
